WEBVTT

00:00.918 --> 00:02.920
EPISODE 58
TOKYO NO. 1 COLONY, PART 5

00:05.798 --> 00:07.842
Domain Expansion.

00:07.883 --> 00:09.718
Chimera Shadow Garden.

00:15.223 --> 00:18.853
Esoteric Technique.
Hollow Wicker Basket.

00:21.062 --> 00:23.774
[NARRATOR] Hollow Wicker Basket
is the origin

00:23.816 --> 00:26.568
of New Shadow Style's
"Simple Domain."

00:26.610 --> 00:29.530
It possesses the ability
to neutralize a domain

00:29.571 --> 00:32.366
and counter
its guaranteed-hit factor.

00:32.407 --> 00:34.117
This won't end well for you.

00:34.159 --> 00:35.160
- [thuds]
- [gasps]

00:35.202 --> 00:36.537
[NARRATOR]
The "Domain Amplification"

00:36.578 --> 00:38.873
used by Jogo and Hanami
in Shibuya

00:38.914 --> 00:41.166
used a domain
capable of guaranteed-hit,

00:41.208 --> 00:42.501
guaranteed-kill technique.

00:42.543 --> 00:43.794
[groans]

00:46.005 --> 00:47.715
[REGGIE]
How was he able to hit me?

00:48.047 --> 00:49.842
[NARRATOR] But they
intentionally left a space

00:49.884 --> 00:51.343
in their cursed techniques

00:51.385 --> 00:54.346
so that Gojo's cursed technique
could flow into it,

00:54.388 --> 00:56.557
neutralizing his Limitless.

00:56.598 --> 01:00.143
However, Hollow Wicker Basket
and Simple Domain aren't capable

01:00.185 --> 01:02.270
of neutralizing
the cursed technique.

01:02.312 --> 01:04.982
So instead, they work
by neutralizing the barrier

01:05.024 --> 01:06.734
that's imbued
with cursed technique.

01:07.066 --> 01:09.110
In this way,
the imbued technique's

01:09.152 --> 01:11.989
guaranteed-hit effect
is nullified.

01:12.031 --> 01:13.699
[groans]

01:14.449 --> 01:17.745
[NARRATOR] But Fushiguro's
domain is incomplete.

01:18.579 --> 01:20.372
Guess that wiped
the sneer off your face.

01:20.414 --> 01:22.081
You damn brat!

01:23.042 --> 01:24.043
[spits]

01:24.209 --> 01:25.669
[NARRATOR]
When he transposed his domain

01:25.711 --> 01:27.504
onto the space of the gymnasium,

01:27.546 --> 01:29.506
an unexpected consequence
happened.

01:29.548 --> 01:31.842
It forced his domain to close.

01:31.884 --> 01:34.595
It is not imbued
with a guaranteed-hit technique.

01:34.636 --> 01:36.179
[grunts]

01:36.221 --> 01:38.097
You're acting
like you've already won!

01:38.139 --> 01:39.433
[groans]

01:39.474 --> 01:41.100
[REGGIE] Now I get it.

01:41.142 --> 01:42.811
[NARRATOR]
Chimera Shadow Garden.

01:42.853 --> 01:44.103
It is currently extending

01:44.145 --> 01:46.398
Fushiguro's Ten Shadows
Technique,

01:46.440 --> 01:47.858
and as it does so,

01:47.900 --> 01:51.820
draws out 120%
of his latent potential.

01:52.529 --> 01:54.531
Unfortunately for Reggie Star,

01:54.573 --> 01:57.367
that very imperfection
is what caught him off-guard.

01:57.409 --> 01:59.327
[REGGIE] Both his clothes
and his shikigami

01:59.369 --> 02:01.914
had physical forms
before striking me.

02:01.956 --> 02:03.498
That means this barrier

02:03.540 --> 02:05.960
isn't imbued
with a guaranteed-hit technique.

02:06.001 --> 02:08.295
The domain's buff
to his technique's abilities

02:08.336 --> 02:09.755
is no joke, though.

02:09.797 --> 02:11.339
This is even worse to deal with

02:11.381 --> 02:13.425
than a simple
guaranteed-hit domain.

02:13.467 --> 02:15.218
If he pulls
that elephant out here

02:15.260 --> 02:16.678
and drenches me in water,

02:16.720 --> 02:19.014
it'll take away
half of my options

02:19.056 --> 02:20.808
and I'll probably lose.

02:23.477 --> 02:24.728
[groans]

02:25.980 --> 02:27.188
[Megumi grunts]

02:28.607 --> 02:30.067
[REGGIE] But, you know,

02:30.109 --> 02:31.693
it's so like me

02:31.735 --> 02:34.195
to make sure
that won't happen.

02:35.781 --> 02:37.532
- [MEGUMI] Nue!
- [Nue screeches]

02:37.574 --> 02:38.575
[Reggie grunts]

02:41.703 --> 02:43.080
Too slow.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.750
I have it figured out.

02:47.126 --> 02:49.003
Yes, I knew it.

02:51.212 --> 02:53.966
I've had to reinforce my footing
with cursed energy

02:54.008 --> 02:55.968
to avoid getting sucked in.

02:58.386 --> 02:59.638
[footsteps splashing]

03:00.806 --> 03:03.308
Because the whole bottom
of this domain

03:03.350 --> 03:05.184
is your shadow, right?

03:05.560 --> 03:08.563
You're able to remove
and store objects and yourself.

03:08.605 --> 03:10.189
That's pretty convenient.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.985
But one thing
kept nagging at me.

03:13.027 --> 03:15.570
"Why doesn't this guy have
more weapons he can use?"

03:15.612 --> 03:18.740
You just use that one paltry
cursed tool over and over.

03:18.782 --> 03:20.450
Maybe it's a low-capacity tool

03:20.492 --> 03:22.953
and you're trying to reserve
as much space for yourself,

03:22.995 --> 03:25.164
just in case you need it
for something later on.

03:25.204 --> 03:26.581
Either that,

03:26.707 --> 03:29.001
or you're being forced to bear
the weight of the objects

03:29.043 --> 03:30.752
that are stored in your shadow.

03:30.794 --> 03:32.504
[struggling]

03:33.547 --> 03:36.050
[REGGIE] Sounds like
the latter was spot-on.

03:36.091 --> 03:38.886
Now I've turned the design
of your domain against you.

03:39.386 --> 03:41.096
With three passenger cars,

03:41.138 --> 03:44.223
your current weight
is approximately 2.4 tons.

03:44.265 --> 03:47.226
Looks like your clones
weren't able to tolerate it.

03:47.268 --> 03:50.480
And I bet you can't even
produce your shikigami now.

03:51.106 --> 03:53.067
Either way, I'll just need
to keep minding

03:53.108 --> 03:54.359
my footing around you,

03:54.902 --> 03:56.695
as I keep adding weight

03:56.737 --> 03:59.114
until you're crushed under it.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.702
[MEGUMI]
Are you stupid or something?

04:05.120 --> 04:07.081
Even if it's incomplete,

04:07.539 --> 04:09.708
a domain is still a domain!

04:10.249 --> 04:12.836
My shadow is everywhere!

04:19.342 --> 04:20.886
[trumpets]

04:22.721 --> 04:24.639
[groans]

04:24.681 --> 04:27.059
Which one of us
will get crushed first?

04:27.101 --> 04:29.895
- Huh, Reggie?!
- [Reggie grunts]

04:30.311 --> 04:32.480
[♪ opening theme song playing]

05:04.387 --> 05:08.600
JUJUTSU KAISEN
THE CULLING GAME PART 1

05:59.818 --> 06:01.236
[whooshing]

06:03.697 --> 06:05.740
[NARRATOR] It is said
that a typical human

06:05.782 --> 06:09.077
will lose consciousness
at five to six Gs.

06:09.661 --> 06:11.830
2.4 tons.

06:11.872 --> 06:14.791
Because Fushiguro
weighed only 60 kilograms,

06:14.833 --> 06:16.584
that meant he was
currently suffering

06:16.626 --> 06:19.378
the equivalent of 40 Gs.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.799
In order to prevent his blood
from pooling in his legs

06:22.841 --> 06:24.009
from the high Gs,

06:24.092 --> 06:26.303
and depriving his brain
of blood flow,

06:26.345 --> 06:28.638
Fushiguro was lowering
his posture,

06:28.680 --> 06:31.350
and reinforcing his body
with cursed energy,

06:31.390 --> 06:33.894
paying special attention
to his legs.

06:36.271 --> 06:40.984
A mature African elephant
weighs three to six tons.

06:42.027 --> 06:45.197
With the domain's improvement
to his technique's accuracy,

06:45.239 --> 06:48.992
Max Elephant accurately
recreated its real weight.

06:49.034 --> 06:50.285
Under that weight,

06:50.493 --> 06:54.331
Reggie Star's right fibula
and heel bone were cracking.

06:54.373 --> 06:55.665
[Reggie groans]

06:56.124 --> 06:58.793
[NARRATOR] Both of them
were now under enormous strain,

06:58.835 --> 07:01.504
and faced the possibility
of being crushed to death

07:01.546 --> 07:02.547
at any second.

07:02.589 --> 07:03.965
[both struggling]

07:04.258 --> 07:05.967
[REGGIE] I screwed up.

07:06.009 --> 07:09.096
I could've won if I had kept
the trucks in reserve.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.471
What do I do?

07:10.513 --> 07:13.058
I got splashed with some water
at the same time,

07:13.100 --> 07:14.893
but my trump card's
still safe.

07:15.434 --> 07:17.062
I could slip into his shadow

07:17.104 --> 07:19.438
and recreate my trump card
inside it.

07:19.480 --> 07:21.358
That would crush him for sure.

07:23.442 --> 07:26.654
No, he's not dismissing
his domain.

07:26.696 --> 07:28.573
But when he does decide
to dismiss it,

07:28.615 --> 07:30.158
that means
anything still in his shadow

07:30.200 --> 07:32.202
is going to be stuck
inside there.

07:32.244 --> 07:34.371
What if I'm stuck
in his shadow forever?

07:34.788 --> 07:36.706
I'll be there
even after he dies!

07:36.748 --> 07:39.167
What's it like
inside his shadow, anyway?

07:39.209 --> 07:40.543
It looks like a liquid,

07:40.585 --> 07:42.421
but what if I can't
breathe in it?

07:42.461 --> 07:43.671
Can I float?

07:43.713 --> 07:44.714
Keep fighting!

07:44.923 --> 07:46.925
Submerging into his shadow
is too risky.

07:47.426 --> 07:48.760
Ah, I'm out of time.

07:48.802 --> 07:51.054
So while stuck in this state,

07:51.096 --> 07:53.807
I have to pull out my trump card

07:53.848 --> 07:55.392
and activate it!

07:56.226 --> 07:57.518
[grunts]

07:57.852 --> 07:58.895
[gasps]

07:59.646 --> 08:02.565
Contractual Re-Creation!

08:02.857 --> 08:05.110
SNAP

08:05.152 --> 08:09.281
[Megumi struggling]

08:09.323 --> 08:10.949
[straining]

08:22.419 --> 08:24.545
[REGGIE]
I didn't make it in time.

08:24.587 --> 08:27.757
And now I know there's no oxygen
inside of his shadow.

08:28.716 --> 08:30.177
No buoyancy

08:30.218 --> 08:31.928
or resistance, either.

08:34.181 --> 08:35.474
I'm just...

08:37.100 --> 08:38.517
sinking.

08:39.811 --> 08:41.396
My consciousness...

08:42.105 --> 08:44.232
is fading.

08:47.402 --> 08:49.821
[Megumi groans] Not yet.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.072
Keep enduring it.

08:51.530 --> 08:53.367
Gotta wait until
I'm sure he's dead

08:53.408 --> 08:55.327
before dismissing the domain!

08:55.369 --> 08:57.871
Then I can expel
whatever's in my shadow.

08:57.912 --> 09:01.082
[straining]

09:24.189 --> 09:26.191
[gasps, coughs]

09:26.233 --> 09:28.360
[coughing]

09:30.195 --> 09:32.197
[REGGIE] The things I recreate,

09:32.864 --> 09:34.657
they disappear
soon after carrying out

09:34.699 --> 09:36.993
whatever command
I gave them to carry out.

09:37.035 --> 09:40.121
However, I didn't give
those cars I sank any commands.

09:40.163 --> 09:43.291
After all, I didn't want them
disappearing on me.

09:43.791 --> 09:46.461
That means I could still issue
them a command if I want.

09:46.503 --> 09:48.713
Something like
"Take me and rise up."

09:49.256 --> 09:50.840
The weight
of one car is gone now,

09:50.882 --> 09:53.760
but it was totally worth it
to save my life.

09:53.801 --> 09:55.554
[Megumi straining]

09:57.889 --> 09:59.349
[REGGIE] Tell you what!

09:59.391 --> 10:02.018
I am man enough to admit it!

10:02.060 --> 10:03.437
You are strong.

10:04.563 --> 10:06.647
But not as strong as me!

10:07.857 --> 10:10.651
Contractual Re-Creation!

10:10.693 --> 10:12.611
[♪ tense music playing]

10:16.116 --> 10:21.455
A 132-square-foot, two-story
wooden frame structure!

10:21.496 --> 10:24.416
The framework alone weighs
at least 30 tons!

10:24.832 --> 10:27.377
And I'm commanding it
to crush you!

10:27.419 --> 10:29.921
[screams]

10:51.192 --> 10:53.528
[Megumi straining]

10:54.154 --> 10:55.447
[music ends]

10:59.493 --> 11:02.036
[Reggie gasps] What happened?

11:02.870 --> 11:06.040
Did I fall back
into his shadow again?

11:06.874 --> 11:09.377
No! I'm in actual water.

11:09.419 --> 11:10.629
How?

11:11.254 --> 11:12.506
It's heavy.

11:12.547 --> 11:15.049
What's the brat trying to do,
strangle me?

11:15.716 --> 11:17.718
What power!

11:17.760 --> 11:19.429
No. That's wrong.

11:19.471 --> 11:22.349
This is from the weight
of those two cars that I added.

11:22.849 --> 11:24.434
This is bad.

11:24.476 --> 11:27.103
This time, I'm really sinking!

11:27.770 --> 11:31.232
I have to dismiss
Contractual Re-Creation!

11:46.623 --> 11:48.500
[gasps]

11:48.542 --> 11:51.461
[panting]

11:51.503 --> 11:52.837
All right.

11:52.879 --> 11:54.631
The community gymnasium.

11:54.673 --> 11:57.716
And in the gym's basement
is a heated swimming pool.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.473
Did he go hiding in a shadow
and dismiss his domain?

12:03.515 --> 12:05.433
That could ' ve forced me
to destroy the floor

12:05.475 --> 12:06.976
and plunge into the pool.

12:07.018 --> 12:08.478
[grunts]

12:09.688 --> 12:11.064
[MEGUMI]
You can't use your receipts

12:11.105 --> 12:13.024
when they're that wet, can you?

12:17.278 --> 12:20.281
[REGGIE] He waited instead of
pursuing me right away.

12:20.323 --> 12:22.576
Does that mean his technique
still needs to recover

12:22.617 --> 12:23.951
after his domain exhausted it?

12:24.827 --> 12:26.329
That's what you think?

12:26.371 --> 12:27.746
Are you sure?

12:28.665 --> 12:30.958
I'm sure that you can't
produce your shikigami

12:31.000 --> 12:32.419
in your current condition.

12:33.752 --> 12:34.962
[MEGUMI] Yeah, that's true.

12:35.046 --> 12:38.341
So you do understand
what comes next, don't ya?

12:39.551 --> 12:42.887
[REGGIE] He's going to use
a shikigami, just not that dog.

12:42.929 --> 12:45.682
But none of his other ones
can deal a decisive blow.

12:45.724 --> 12:47.434
Fine. Use it!

12:47.475 --> 12:49.143
The moment
that you let up on me,

12:49.185 --> 12:51.104
I'll finish you
with a counterattack!

13:22.427 --> 13:25.722
[both grunting]

13:41.571 --> 13:44.491
You thought Demon Dog
was some weak shikigami?

13:45.032 --> 13:46.326
You were wrong.

13:47.327 --> 13:48.995
What did I tell you before?

13:49.036 --> 13:51.205
We sorcerers are all liars.

13:51.247 --> 13:52.373
- [groans]
- [thuds]

13:53.333 --> 13:54.959
JUJUTSU KAISEN

13:58.379 --> 13:59.922
JUJUTSU KAISEN

14:00.006 --> 14:02.925
[♪ tranquil music playing,
Camille Saint-Saëns "Le Cygne"]

14:08.556 --> 14:10.141
[REGGIE] The domain.

14:10.183 --> 14:11.476
The pool.

14:11.892 --> 14:13.144
All to convince me

14:13.186 --> 14:15.522
you couldn't use
that dog anymore.

14:16.022 --> 14:18.899
You didn't escape
into this gymnasium.

14:18.941 --> 14:20.652
You lured me into it.

14:21.736 --> 14:24.698
To think I'd let
a modern sorcerer,

14:24.739 --> 14:27.784
and a brat at that,
get the better of me.

14:29.868 --> 14:31.912
Nue can't fly that far
carrying me,

14:31.954 --> 14:33.247
so I couldn't escape.

14:33.707 --> 14:36.042
I've had trouble
with that before.

14:41.756 --> 14:42.881
Tell me,

14:42.923 --> 14:44.925
how are you connected
to Tengen?

14:49.514 --> 14:51.307
Who are you talking about?

14:51.974 --> 14:54.853
Oh, right, Tengen.

14:54.893 --> 14:57.271
That hermit
would still be alive.

14:57.980 --> 15:00.441
Must be history's
greatest shut-in.

15:00.483 --> 15:02.276
Okay. That's enough.

15:04.278 --> 15:05.739
Reggie said Tengen's claims

15:05.780 --> 15:07.948
about the Culling Game
were a bluff.

15:09.200 --> 15:11.285
I'd be smart
to consider the possibility

15:11.327 --> 15:14.121
Tengen and Kenjaku
are secretly connected,

15:14.163 --> 15:16.624
and that they're both lying
about their endgames.

15:17.208 --> 15:20.336
But that doesn't seem likely
from Reggie's reaction.

15:23.423 --> 15:24.716
Kogane,

15:25.091 --> 15:29.095
transfer all my points over
to this little brat.

15:29.136 --> 15:30.513
[KOGANE] Okay.

15:31.890 --> 15:33.182
Congratulations,

15:33.224 --> 15:36.269
you have been granted 41 points
by Reggie Star.

15:36.310 --> 15:37.771
And in return?

15:38.354 --> 15:41.065
Must you assume
I have some evil plot?

15:41.107 --> 15:44.318
I want to do at least
one good deed before I die.

15:44.943 --> 15:47.530
By the way,
I'm just a spectator here.

15:47.572 --> 15:50.742
Kenjaku and I weren't
ever close friends.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.243
But I do like this game.

15:52.285 --> 15:54.328
It certainly
makes things interesting.

15:54.913 --> 15:57.123
That's my intuition anyway.

15:58.416 --> 16:00.418
Now do me a favor.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.796
After all, you did kill me.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.298
The favor is,

16:05.715 --> 16:07.467
let fate toy with you

16:07.966 --> 16:10.219
before you die like a fool.

16:10.261 --> 16:13.347
♪

16:33.451 --> 16:36.036
[KOGANE] You have gained
five points for a kill.

16:38.122 --> 16:39.958
[whooshing]

16:40.792 --> 16:42.168
[sips, grunts]

16:49.049 --> 16:50.259
I got him!

16:50.844 --> 16:52.929
Nope! 'Cause you
dropped your guard!

16:54.138 --> 16:55.723
You think you're Mr. Tough Guy?

16:55.765 --> 16:57.224
What the hell!

16:57.266 --> 16:59.853
Ugh! Why is your whole body
covered in lotion?

16:59.894 --> 17:01.562
It might actually be sauce.

17:01.604 --> 17:03.147
Just die!

17:03.690 --> 17:05.191
[groans]

17:05.232 --> 17:07.067
I pray it's only sauce!

17:07.527 --> 17:09.487
Seriously, what's with this guy?

17:09.529 --> 17:10.989
I've blown him up a lot!

17:11.029 --> 17:14.116
I feel like I've killed him
at least five times.

17:14.158 --> 17:16.953
So how come he has
so little damage?

17:16.995 --> 17:18.579
SO LITTLE.

17:18.621 --> 17:19.873
What's wrong with sauce?

17:20.456 --> 17:23.001
[IORI] Even his giant
head wound has healed up.

17:23.626 --> 17:25.043
But he hasn't shown any signs

17:25.085 --> 17:27.005
of using
reverse cursed techniques

17:27.045 --> 17:28.214
like I do.

17:28.548 --> 17:30.591
I don't get
what's going on with him.

17:30.925 --> 17:32.385
Player Hazenoki.

17:32.426 --> 17:33.553
What'd you want?

17:33.594 --> 17:34.888
I regret to inform you

17:34.929 --> 17:36.973
that player Reggie Star
has just died.

17:37.015 --> 17:38.056
Huh?

17:40.643 --> 17:42.102
[exclaims] Where you goin'?

17:42.144 --> 17:43.521
[IORI] I'm goin' home.

17:43.563 --> 17:44.772
I'm sick of this.

17:44.814 --> 17:46.733
[TAKABA] Oh. Well, take a bath!

17:46.774 --> 17:48.401
And brush your teeth!

17:49.736 --> 17:50.778
[gasps]

17:51.404 --> 17:54.281
Hey! How about
giving me your points?

17:54.323 --> 17:55.575
Don't follow me.

17:55.616 --> 17:56.784
Oh, come on!

17:56.826 --> 17:59.161
Just think of it
as paying it forward.

17:59.203 --> 18:00.246
Just die.

18:00.538 --> 18:02.916
[NARRATOR] Takaba's
cursed technique, Comedian,

18:02.957 --> 18:05.334
takes whatever he's convinced
would be funny,

18:05.376 --> 18:07.294
and turns it into a reality.

18:07.336 --> 18:11.257
Even Satoru Gojo is incapable
of opposing this technique.

18:13.259 --> 18:18.056
Yet Takaba is utterly clueless
as to how his technique works.

18:18.890 --> 18:21.684
[Remi panting]

18:26.773 --> 18:28.816
[REMI]
I don't get it, I don't get it!

18:28.858 --> 18:32.110
Ever since I became an adult,
I hardly understand anything.

18:32.152 --> 18:35.073
[panting]

18:37.825 --> 18:40.578
I've heard that all men
are actually wolves.

18:40.620 --> 18:41.829
But it's always those wolves

18:41.871 --> 18:44.122
who take care of
the confusing stuff for me.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.797
It's a win-win situation.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.423
The wolves love being in charge,

18:52.465 --> 18:54.717
and I love not thinking
about anything.

18:54.759 --> 18:57.762
Men always want to do stuff
for me because I'm so cute.

19:01.682 --> 19:04.435
[panting]

19:04.477 --> 19:07.730
The wolves
will always, always--

19:07.772 --> 19:10.274
- [snarls]
- [gasps]

19:16.489 --> 19:18.825
[TSUMIKI] Megumi, don't.

19:25.623 --> 19:27.083
[REMI] You're not killing me?

19:27.708 --> 19:29.043
[footsteps receding]

19:35.215 --> 19:36.968
[MEGUMI] Damn it, sis.

19:38.094 --> 19:39.137
[thuds]

19:40.346 --> 19:42.180
Shut up already.

19:49.772 --> 19:52.232
[♪ ethereal music playing]

20:02.118 --> 20:04.996
[NARRATOR] Events progressed
quickly in the Sendai Colony,

20:05.038 --> 20:06.789
far outstripping those of Tokyo.

20:07.165 --> 20:10.459
They also started
to become increasingly fierce.

20:12.378 --> 20:14.047
Dhruv Lakdawalla.

20:14.088 --> 20:16.549
Current points, 91.

20:16.590 --> 20:18.968
This is his second incarnation.

20:19.802 --> 20:22.138
He's an old man
who single-handedly

20:22.180 --> 20:25.808
conquered this archipelago
during the Civil War of Wa.

20:25.850 --> 20:28.561
He possesses
two autonomous shikigami,

20:28.602 --> 20:32.523
and the orbit of those shikigami
determines his domain.

20:35.442 --> 20:37.070
Ryu Ishigori.

20:37.111 --> 20:39.446
Current points, 77.

20:40.238 --> 20:42.575
He has the greatest
cursed energy firepower

20:42.616 --> 20:45.078
among any other remaining
player in the game.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.288
Takako Uro.

20:48.330 --> 20:50.290
Current points, 70.

20:50.332 --> 20:52.043
She was originally the captain

20:52.085 --> 20:54.503
of the Sun, Moon,
and Stars Squad.

20:54.545 --> 20:56.714
Assassins for the Fujiwara Clan.

20:57.131 --> 21:00.218
Her technique can
manipulate the sky.

21:01.635 --> 21:02.929
Kurourushi.

21:02.970 --> 21:05.098
Current points, 54.

21:05.514 --> 21:08.684
A cockroach cursed spirit
that Kenjaku freed

21:08.726 --> 21:11.729
from the control
of cursed spirit manipulation.

21:12.063 --> 21:15.608
It ranks as a previously
registered special-grade.

21:16.943 --> 21:18.611
It's currently lying dormant

21:18.652 --> 21:20.780
until certain conditions
are met.

21:22.115 --> 21:24.282
There was no alliance
between them,

21:24.324 --> 21:27.536
but their complex compatibility
and opposing strength

21:27.578 --> 21:30.330
led them into
a four-way stalemate.

21:30.748 --> 21:33.209
But one of those pillars...

21:33.251 --> 21:34.460
[slashes]

21:34.835 --> 21:36.045
...has fallen.

21:37.295 --> 21:39.173
Yuta Okkotsu.

21:39.215 --> 21:41.717
Current points, 35.

21:41.759 --> 21:43.636
Three months
after the Night Parade

21:43.677 --> 21:44.971
of a Hundred Demons,

21:45.012 --> 21:47.765
he blossomed
as a special-grade sorcerer.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.642
He is a modern sorcerer,

21:49.683 --> 21:51.477
rivaling the abilities
of even...

21:51.769 --> 21:54.021
Satoru Gojo.

21:55.313 --> 21:57.483
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:26.155 --> 23:28.366
[YUTA] I'll obtain
400 points on my own.

23:28.406 --> 23:30.326
[RIKA] Which would
you like, Yuta?

23:30.368 --> 23:31.827
[KOGANE]
It's called Kurourushi!

23:31.869 --> 23:34.830
- [YUTA] I'll take it all!
- [RIKA] Give me back Yuta!

23:34.872 --> 23:38.000
[YUTA] I refuse to let you
kill your best friend twice.

23:38.042 --> 23:39.960
NEXT EPISODE
SENDAI COLONY
